*************************************
* Enviroment Setup
*************************************
- Install Microsoft Visual Studio 2012 with latest updates
   http://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=34673
- Install latest Android SDK (Windows version)
   http://www.cnblogs.com/bjzhanghao/archive/2012/11/14/android-platform-sdk-download-mirror.html
- Install JDK 1.7
   http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk7-downloads-1880260.html
   Install to C:\JDK
- Install ANT
   http://ant.apache.org/bindownload.cgi?Preferred=http%3A%2F%2Fmirrors.cnnic.cn%2Fapache%2F
- Install latest Android NDK
   https://developer.android.com/tools/sdk/ndk/index.html#Installing
- Set environment variables
   JAVA_HOME=<JDK install dir>
   ANT_HOME=<ant install dir>
   ANDROID_SDK=<android sdk dir>
   add <ant install dir>\bin;<android ndk dir>\;<android sdk dir>\platform-tools\ to PATH

*************************************
* Build
*************************************

IMPORTANT!!! First try to build win32 to see if everything is running OK!

- Win32 
* Run msvc2012
* Open Paper3D/examples/background/application/configs/msvc2012/Background.sln in msvc2012

- Android
* Run cmd.exe in win32
* Enter Tech/configs/android
* Enter build.bat debug 
* Enter Paper3D/configs/android
* Enter build.bat debug 
* Enter Paper3D/examples/background/application/configs/android
* Enter build.bat debug and it will generate background-debug.apk in ..\..\bin\android

